column1: Labour Force Status by Sex by Regional Council (Qrtly-Mar/Jun/Sep/Dec)

On 1 November 2010, the new Auckland territorial authority (TA) replaced the existing: Rodney District, North Shore City, Auckland City, Waitakere City, Manukau City, Papakura District, and part of Franklin District councils.
The changes were introduced in the release for the June 2011 quarter and backcast for the March 2011 quarter.
This has resulted in minor changes in the boundary between the Auckland and Waikato regions. The new boundaries do not significantly affect measures from the Household Labour Force Survey (HLFS).
